529
00:24:27,370 --> 00:24:29,740
People should improve as they get older.

530
00:24:30,470 --> 00:24:32,240
- This? Let's go.
- Where do we need to go?

531
00:24:32,240 --> 00:24:33,410
- Let's go.
- What?

532
00:24:33,410 --> 00:24:35,680
- Let's get out of here. I don't know.
- Where are we going?

533
00:24:35,880 --> 00:24:37,980
- Just the heels.
- Yes, move the heels.

534
00:24:37,980 --> 00:24:39,480
Gwan Hee, we cracked it.

535
00:24:40,950 --> 00:24:43,180
(Team P2 escapes.)

536
00:24:43,850 --> 00:24:45,120
- Seung Jin.
- Hey.

537
00:24:45,120 --> 00:24:46,250
- Nice to see you.
- Have you been well?

538
00:24:47,850 --> 00:24:48,920
Who knew we'd meet here?

539
00:24:48,920 --> 00:24:51,060
You jerks. You guys didn't keep in touch.

540
00:24:51,390 --> 00:24:53,390
You should've given me a heads-up
if you were going to join the show.

541
00:24:53,630 --> 00:24:54,890
I mean,

542
00:24:54,890 --> 00:24:56,830
I'm older than you. So I get a pass.

543
00:24:57,060 --> 00:24:58,470
You should've given me a heads-up.
You're my juniors.

544
00:25:00,670 --> 00:25:01,870
- Hey.
- Help us first.

545
00:25:02,170 --> 00:25:03,400
- Wait.
- Hold on.

546
00:25:09,640 --> 00:25:10,980
We figured out the answer,

547
00:25:10,980 --> 00:25:12,780
but we couldn't untie the ropes.
It drove us crazy.

548
00:25:12,780 --> 00:25:14,950
The last thing we struggled to free
was my ankle.

549
00:25:14,980 --> 00:25:17,380
I thought at this rate,
Jin Ho might cut my ankle off.

550
00:25:17,380 --> 00:25:19,090
"I'll put it back later, Xitsuh."

551
00:25:19,890 --> 00:25:20,890
We got it.

552
00:25:21,390 --> 00:25:23,020
The knot is insanely tight.

553
00:25:23,020 --> 00:25:24,190
- We need to cut off his ankle.
- Who...

554
00:25:24,460 --> 00:25:26,160
No, you can't do that. You got it.

555
00:25:26,160 --> 00:25:27,160
(Groaning)

556
00:25:27,160 --> 00:25:28,160
- We got it.
- Darn it.

557
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:29,700
You can do this. Please!

558
00:25:29,700 --> 00:25:31,260
- You can do this.
- We got it!

559
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:34,300
- We got it.
- I'm a man!

560
00:25:34,300 --> 00:25:35,840
- All right.
- Yes.

561
00:25:35,840 --> 00:25:37,240
- This is good.
- I got it.

562
00:25:38,570 --> 00:25:39,570
- We got it.
- Darn it.

563
00:25:39,570 --> 00:25:40,740
Hey, let's hurry.

564
00:25:40,740 --> 00:25:42,040
I'm wearing my shoe backward.

565
00:25:46,880 --> 00:25:48,210
Yes!

566
00:25:50,220 --> 00:25:51,280
- Let's run.
- That hurts.

567
00:25:51,680 --> 00:25:54,920
- We're the only ones who cracked it.
- Are you okay?

568
00:25:55,020 --> 00:25:56,060
- No one cracked it.
- Right.

569
00:25:56,060 --> 00:25:57,360
- Let's be proud.
- Seriously.

570
00:25:57,360 --> 00:25:59,090
We got out of there by using our brain!

571
00:25:59,460 --> 00:26:01,060
We're just slow at physical things.

572
00:26:01,060 --> 00:26:03,000
- Be careful.
- We still got it.

573
00:26:03,060 --> 00:26:04,100
That's good.

574
00:26:04,260 --> 00:26:06,400
We have a basketball player
coming after us. We must hurry.

575
00:26:06,600 --> 00:26:07,870
He's a super fast runner.

576
00:26:08,670 --> 00:26:10,640
Team Rookie hasn't escaped yet.

577
00:26:11,170 --> 00:26:14,340
(Only two teams remain now.)

578
00:26:14,670 --> 00:26:16,110
My legs are tied up.

579
00:26:17,780 --> 00:26:18,980
I can't untie the ropes around my legs.

580
00:26:18,980 --> 00:26:20,080
Same here.

581
00:26:20,580 --> 00:26:22,380
Darn it. These are connected.

582
00:26:26,250 --> 00:26:28,960
I'll do this for you. Take off your shoes,
so you can pull out your legs.

583
00:26:28,960 --> 00:26:31,260
I don't think
that's going to help me get out of these.

584
00:26:31,420 --> 00:26:32,560
No, it will help.

585
00:26:34,730 --> 00:26:36,100
- Will it help?
- Yes.

586
00:26:49,080 --> 00:26:50,780
- Are they out?
- Yes, just one.

587
00:26:54,780 --> 00:26:56,580
- Just one.
- Wait.

588
00:26:56,980 --> 00:26:57,980
That's it.

589
00:27:05,220 --> 00:27:06,590
- Where? Your feet?
- Not there.

590
00:27:06,590 --> 00:27:08,090
- My feet are tied.
- Where? Your feet?

591
00:27:08,090 --> 00:27:09,100
Yes.

592
00:27:10,930 --> 00:27:13,100
We should... It's going to hurt.

593
00:27:13,370 --> 00:27:14,400
Just pull it.

594
00:27:15,340 --> 00:27:17,640
We got it. Okay.

595
00:27:17,840 --> 00:27:19,570
Don't even put on your shoes.
Let's just go.

596
00:27:19,940 --> 00:27:20,970
We don't have time.

597
00:27:21,140 --> 00:27:22,210
Run.

598
00:27:22,380 --> 00:27:23,510
There.

599
00:27:24,510 --> 00:27:25,550
Wait, there's one around your body?

600
00:27:25,550 --> 00:27:26,750
We need to pull his body out.

601
00:27:26,750 --> 00:27:29,180
- Let's just pull it out. That won't work.
- Let's pull it up.

602
00:27:29,250 --> 00:27:30,880
Let's pull it up.

603
00:27:31,550 --> 00:27:33,350
To the side. I'm sorry.

604
00:27:34,550 --> 00:27:36,260
- Yes.
- We need to free the other foot.

605
00:27:36,260 --> 00:27:37,890
- Take off your shoes.
- We have to pull it out.

606
00:27:38,090 --> 00:27:39,330
- My shoes...
- Take them off.

607
00:27:39,390 --> 00:27:40,630
No, we can do this.

608
00:27:41,560 --> 00:27:42,930
I'm holding the chair.

609
00:27:47,070 --> 00:27:48,700
They tied up his legs way too tightly.

610
00:27:50,340 --> 00:27:51,340
We got it.

611
00:27:52,240 --> 00:27:53,340
- We got it.
- Let's go.

612
00:27:53,340 --> 00:27:54,670
- Got it?
- Let's go.

613
00:27:54,770 --> 00:27:56,580
- Just grab them.
- Let's go.

614
00:28:00,650 --> 00:28:01,650
Darn.

615
00:28:08,920 --> 00:28:12,890
(The last team left, Team R)

616
00:28:15,030 --> 00:28:17,230
(Team C escapes.)

617
00:28:17,230 --> 00:28:18,230
Darn it.

618
00:28:24,200 --> 00:28:25,570
"I'm safe."

619
00:28:25,570 --> 00:28:28,070
That's when I got a rush of dopamine.

620
00:28:28,340 --> 00:28:30,140
We're Team Challenger.

621
00:28:30,140 --> 00:28:33,110
But all of us have participated
in similar shows like this.

622
00:28:33,110 --> 00:28:34,980
But Team Rookie...

623
00:28:34,980 --> 00:28:37,380
