624
00:28:37,380 --> 00:28:39,690
Experiencing it, hearing about it,
or watching it are all different.

625
00:28:39,690 --> 00:28:41,850
So once we got out of the ropes
and started running,

626
00:28:42,020 --> 00:28:43,720
I looked at them and thought,

627
00:28:43,720 --> 00:28:46,960
"They're going to learn firsthand
how tough it is to compete here."

628
00:28:46,960 --> 00:28:48,130
That's what I was thinking.

629
00:28:49,330 --> 00:28:50,360
We're almost there.

630
00:28:52,170 --> 00:28:53,870
Hurry. Let's get in.

631
00:28:57,240 --> 00:29:00,410
(They get on the last remaining vehicle.)

632
00:29:01,170 --> 00:29:02,210
Oh, I'm so relieved.

633
00:29:03,080 --> 00:29:04,080
Right.

634
00:29:08,850 --> 00:29:09,880
That was hard.

635
00:29:12,650 --> 00:29:13,790
We're safe.

636
00:29:14,350 --> 00:29:15,720
We won't have to sleep outdoors.

637
00:29:23,760 --> 00:29:25,000
We're the first ones.

638
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:26,030
(P1 was the 1st one to set out.)

639
00:29:26,030 --> 00:29:28,500
I hope we finish first
on our last day too.

640
00:29:30,870 --> 00:29:32,710
We were off to a great start.

641
00:29:32,940 --> 00:29:34,940
I thought this was a preview that...

642
00:29:34,940 --> 00:29:37,110
our team would be able to beat
the other teams.

643
00:29:39,350 --> 00:29:40,450
Let's hurry.

644
00:29:41,280 --> 00:29:42,320
Gosh, it's freezing.

645
00:29:44,480 --> 00:29:45,520
Darn, where is it?

646
00:29:47,050 --> 00:29:48,190
Is that the place?

647
00:29:48,290 --> 00:29:50,760
- All the way at the top?
- I see a four-story building.

648
00:29:53,730 --> 00:29:55,360
Do we have the whole place to ourselves?

649
00:30:20,090 --> 00:30:21,590
What?
There are so many spots for secret talks.

650
00:30:21,590 --> 00:30:23,620
Right. We won't be able to find people
when they talk in secret.

651
00:30:23,760 --> 00:30:26,030
It was a magnificent building.

652
00:30:26,030 --> 00:30:29,630
I just knew that
crazy games awaited us this season.

653
00:30:30,060 --> 00:30:31,230
(Several days later)

654
00:30:31,230 --> 00:30:33,130
- You're joking, right?
- Don't be ridiculous.

655
00:30:33,130 --> 00:30:34,230
I'll never let go.

656
00:30:34,230 --> 00:30:35,570
- Hey. Stop it.
- I'll kill you. Let go.

657
00:30:35,570 --> 00:30:36,570
Let go of me!

658
00:30:36,570 --> 00:30:37,840
- Let go!
- Get lost.

659
00:30:37,840 --> 00:30:38,940
Darn it.

660
00:30:39,070 --> 00:30:40,470
Hey! Wait.

661
00:30:40,470 --> 00:30:42,640
Come on. Hurry up!

662
00:30:42,640 --> 00:30:43,740
- That hurts.
- Hurry.

663
00:30:44,880 --> 00:30:46,310
Get him!

664
00:30:46,310 --> 00:30:47,480
Get him!

665
00:30:47,780 --> 00:30:49,450
This is infuriating. Darn.

666
00:30:52,650 --> 00:30:55,090
(Team P1 comes in 1st.)

667
00:30:55,190 --> 00:31:00,790
(Main hall)

668
00:31:00,790 --> 00:31:04,100
That looks like something we have to break
on the day of the ambush.

669
00:31:04,860 --> 00:31:06,830
When we walked in...

670
00:31:06,830 --> 00:31:08,530
I guess we're sitting by team.

671
00:31:08,530 --> 00:31:09,570
We're Team Red.

672
00:31:10,340 --> 00:31:13,010
The seats were divided by team.

673
00:31:15,470 --> 00:31:18,810
It gave us a sense of belonging
and developed a bond within the team.

674
00:31:18,810 --> 00:31:20,780
I thought we'd have great teamwork.

675
00:31:28,520 --> 00:31:31,490
First of all,
there were profile cards on the table.

676
00:31:31,490 --> 00:31:34,960
That's how we figured out who was who.

677
00:31:34,960 --> 00:31:37,200
We learned more about the other players.

678
00:31:37,200 --> 00:31:38,730
It was a good chance
to get an idea who they were.

679
00:31:41,530 --> 00:31:44,240
Welcome to the Bloody Mansion.

680
00:31:45,300 --> 00:31:48,170
You will now choose your team's fund.

681
00:31:48,510 --> 00:31:49,940
The team funds are calculated...

682
00:31:50,140 --> 00:31:53,080
by categorizing individual incomes
into tax brackets...

683
00:31:53,910 --> 00:31:56,280
based on the 2025
Comprehensive Income Tax...

684
00:31:56,580 --> 00:31:58,750
and adding all those amounts together.

685
00:31:59,320 --> 00:32:01,450
The team with the highest amount...

686
00:32:01,490 --> 00:32:03,060
has 280,000 dollars.

687
00:32:03,560 --> 00:32:06,430
The team with the lowest amount
has 180,000 dollars.

688
00:32:08,190 --> 00:32:10,800
Discuss with your team to decide
which team's fund you want to choose.

689
00:32:10,900 --> 00:32:13,270
Then a representative of the team
will enter the Voting Room...

690
00:32:13,270 --> 00:32:14,870
and choose the team's fund.

691
00:32:14,870 --> 00:32:16,540
- It's for the team fund.
- It's for the team fund.

692
00:32:16,540 --> 00:32:19,010
Money plays an important role here.

693
00:32:19,010 --> 00:32:21,770
We can buy extra votes with money.

694
00:32:21,770 --> 00:32:25,140
Having a lot of money will allow us
to buy items and give us an advantage.

695
00:32:26,580 --> 00:32:27,950
It's highly likely...

696
00:32:28,080 --> 00:32:29,720
that Jin Ho has the most money.

697
00:32:29,780 --> 00:32:31,980
He recently posted it on his social media.

698
00:32:31,980 --> 00:32:33,320
- That he won second place.
- Right.

699
00:32:33,320 --> 00:32:35,390
- That was probably this year.
- It was this year.

700
00:32:35,390 --> 00:32:36,560
- What about last year?
- Last year?

701
00:32:36,560 --> 00:32:37,890
- It's based on last year's income.
- Yes.

702
00:32:37,890 --> 00:32:40,290
- Last year's income?
- Last year...

703
00:32:40,560 --> 00:32:42,460
I can sort of guess...

704
00:32:42,460 --> 00:32:45,160
how much money
professional poker players make.

705
00:32:45,160 --> 00:32:47,500
But their income fluctuates a lot
every year.

706
00:32:47,500 --> 00:32:50,470
I tried to figure out
how much Jin Ho made last year.

707
00:32:50,570 --> 00:32:55,240
We had to make a guess
to snatch 280,000 dollars.

708
00:32:55,310 --> 00:32:57,380
- Wait.
- I bet Kwak Beom makes a lot of money.

709
00:32:57,380 --> 00:32:59,210
- Him too.
- Lee Gwan Hee makes good money too.

710
00:32:59,210 --> 00:33:00,310
- Right.
- Yes.

711
00:33:00,310 --> 00:33:01,510
He's a doctor.

712
00:33:01,780 --> 00:33:03,320
Wait, this is tough.

713
00:33:03,320 --> 00:33:04,950
Think about it. His annual salary is high.

714
00:33:04,980 --> 00:33:08,320
We were considering Team P3 and Team R.

715
00:33:09,460 --> 00:33:11,160
But our team's fund
might be 280,000 dollars.

716
00:33:11,320 --> 00:33:12,690
- That's possible.
- It could be us.

717
00:33:12,760 --> 00:33:14,760
- How much did you put down?
- I put down 50,000 dollars.

718
00:33:14,760 --> 00:33:16,460
- You did? I put down 200,000 dollars.
- I put down 80,000 dollars.

719
00:33:16,460 --> 00:33:17,560
I put down 1.5 million dollars.

720
00:33:22,070 --> 00:33:23,140
- Wait.
- One and a half million dollars?

721
00:33:23,770 --> 00:33:24,770
One and a half million dollars?

722
00:33:24,770 --> 00:33:27,470
There weren't a lot of people
who could exceed...

723
00:33:27,470 --> 00:33:28,770
Sang Min's annual salary.

724
00:33:28,840 --> 00:33:31,240
- Let's pick us for 280,000 dollars.
- Yes. Let's do that.

725
00:33:31,240 --> 00:33:32,450
- Let's pick us.
- Yes.

726
00:33:32,950 --> 00:33:34,750
We didn't have to gamble...

727
00:33:34,750 --> 00:33:36,050
without having all the information.

728
00:33:36,520 --> 00:33:38,880
I told them I made good money,
so we should pick ours.

729
00:33:39,050 --> 00:33:40,790
- You should go.
- Me?

730
00:33:40,790 --> 00:33:42,220
(Their discussion for the team fund
is over.)

731
00:33:42,220 --> 00:33:44,560
I don't think anyone put down
over 1.5 million dollars.

732
00:33:48,130 --> 00:33:50,400
(Voting Room)

733
00:33:56,200 --> 00:33:57,200
Hello.

734
00:33:57,870 --> 00:34:00,140
Team P1, you were the 1st to arrive.

735
00:34:00,140 --> 00:34:03,010
Please pick 1 of these 5 team funds.

736
00:34:07,450 --> 00:34:10,420
I will now reveal the team fund
for Team P1.

737
00:34:10,650 --> 00:34:12,350
Please.

738
00:34:13,390 --> 00:34:14,490
Please.

739
00:34:14,890 --> 00:34:19,490
Please. Give us more.

740
00:34:19,490 --> 00:34:20,560
Keep going, please.

741
00:34:21,330 --> 00:34:22,460
Yes.

742
00:34:22,700 --> 00:34:25,100
One, two, three, four, five,
six, seven, eight, nine.

743
00:34:25,770 --> 00:34:28,100
You chose Team P1's team fund...

744
00:34:28,100 --> 00:34:29,840
which stands at 270,000 dollars.

745
00:34:30,340 --> 00:34:31,570
Thank you.

746
00:34:32,670 --> 00:34:33,870
We had the second highest team fund.

747
00:34:33,870 --> 00:34:35,110
It wasn't a big difference.

748
00:34:35,540 --> 00:34:36,910
(Team P1)

749
00:34:36,910 --> 00:34:39,650
(150,000 dollars, 70,000 dollars,
30,000 dollars, 20,000 dollars)

750
00:34:39,650 --> 00:34:42,450
(Team P1's team fund: 270,000 dollars)

751
00:34:43,150 --> 00:34:45,920
I see warm coffee.

752
00:34:46,120 --> 00:34:47,550
- Gosh. Hey.
- Yes!

753
00:34:48,550 --> 00:34:50,660
(Welcome food awaits the team
in 1st place.)

754
00:34:50,660 --> 00:34:51,760
Hold on.

755
00:34:57,000 --> 00:34:58,230
Gosh, it's so refreshing.

756
00:34:59,430 --> 00:35:01,800
- Gosh, this is good. Yes.
- It's good, right?

757
00:35:04,540 --> 00:35:06,440
- This lemon one is nice.
- It's good, right?

758
00:35:07,640 --> 00:35:09,480
The one with the lemon is really good.

759
00:35:10,380 --> 00:35:12,980
Let's eat all the lemon ones
and get rid of the plate.

760
00:35:12,980 --> 00:35:14,410
I know this for sure.

761
00:35:14,550 --> 00:35:15,820
We shouldn't be nice on this show.

762
00:35:17,180 --> 00:35:20,550
Thinking about the first season
infuriates me.

763
00:35:20,590 --> 00:35:22,590
Afterward, I became a glutton.

764
00:35:25,690 --> 00:35:26,760
It's a castle.

765
00:35:26,990 --> 00:35:29,800
- I don't want to get eliminated.
- I can't be eliminated...

766
00:35:29,830 --> 00:35:31,160
now that I've seen this.

767
00:35:32,300 --> 00:35:33,630
Hello.

768
00:35:33,630 --> 00:35:35,430
(Team P2, in 2nd place)

769
00:35:35,430 --> 00:35:36,570
You guys are in second place?

770
00:35:37,240 --> 00:35:38,240
- You're in second place?
- Thanks to you.

771
00:35:38,240 --> 00:35:39,710
- Because I helped you?
- It's all thanks to you.

772
00:35:39,710 --> 00:35:40,740
You'd better return the favor.

773
00:35:40,740 --> 00:35:41,870
- I will.
- Yes.

774
00:35:41,940 --> 00:35:43,910
Before our team got out of there
after untying the ropes,

775
00:35:43,910 --> 00:35:45,950
I told Team P2 the answer.

776
00:35:46,050 --> 00:35:48,450
They were the second team to arrive
thanks to me.

777
00:35:48,450 --> 00:35:49,550
Then they ought to pay me back.

778
00:35:50,280 --> 00:35:52,020
- You're in second place?
- Thanks to you.

779
00:35:52,020 --> 00:35:53,220
When I saw...

780
00:35:53,220 --> 00:35:54,520
Seung Jin's team walking in after us,

781
00:35:54,520 --> 00:35:57,290
I thought we'd be able
to win them over to our side.

782
00:35:57,360 --> 00:35:58,920
They'll pay us back for sure.

783
00:36:00,390 --> 00:36:01,690
The bio cards are here.

784
00:36:02,800 --> 00:36:03,960
Let's see.

785
00:36:03,960 --> 00:36:05,700
Here's Sang Min's card.
This is Jin Ho's card.

786
00:36:05,700 --> 00:36:07,530
I bet they also made a lot of money.

787
00:36:07,530 --> 00:36:08,730
He's a doctor.

788
00:36:08,730 --> 00:36:10,340
Don't basketball players make
a lot of money?

789
00:36:10,340 --> 00:36:11,340
Well, I wouldn't know, though.

790
00:36:11,340 --> 00:36:12,370
- Gwan Hee...
- Yes.

791
00:36:12,370 --> 00:36:13,370
He makes a lot of money.

792
00:36:13,410 --> 00:36:16,410
I know that Gwan Hee makes
between 400,000 and 500,000 dollars.

793
00:36:16,410 --> 00:36:18,940
I was thinking
about picking Team Rookie's fund.

794
00:36:20,180 --> 00:36:21,580
Do you want my advice?

795
00:36:23,120 --> 00:36:25,080
I bet Jin Ho is the jackpot.

796
00:36:25,180 --> 00:36:26,720
I doubt Gwan Hee makes that much money.

797
00:36:26,720 --> 00:36:27,850
He makes a six-figure annual salary.

798
00:36:27,850 --> 00:36:30,220
I know that. Sure,
he makes a six-figure annual salary,

799
00:36:30,220 --> 00:36:31,920
But it can't be more than
400,000 or 500,000 dollars.

800
00:36:33,130 --> 00:36:34,860
Sang Min from Team P1 said...

801
00:36:34,860 --> 00:36:36,460
having 1 person with just 400,000 dollars
wouldn't do much.

802
00:36:36,560 --> 00:36:38,200
He kept telling me that.

803
00:36:38,230 --> 00:36:39,670
He had a point.

804
00:36:39,670 --> 00:36:41,470
I'll vote for Team P3.

805
00:36:41,470 --> 00:36:42,540
Me too.

806
00:36:42,540 --> 00:36:44,170
- I do think that's a better choice.
- Should we go with that?

807
00:36:44,170 --> 00:36:45,540
- Go ahead. You go.
- Okay.

808
00:36:46,270 --> 00:36:47,370
Let us know.

809
00:36:49,940 --> 00:36:51,740
Team P2, you're the 2nd team to arrive.

810
00:36:51,740 --> 00:36:53,910
Please pick the team fund you want.

811
00:36:56,350 --> 00:36:59,190
I will now reveal the team fund
for Team P3.

812
00:36:59,250 --> 00:37:01,350
Team P3's fund...

813
00:37:01,850 --> 00:37:03,290
stands at 200,000 dollars.

814
00:37:04,860 --> 00:37:06,530
It was beyond what I had imagined,
actually.

815
00:37:06,530 --> 00:37:10,160
On this show, 10,000 and 20,000 dollars
can mean either survival or elimination.

816
00:37:10,800 --> 00:37:12,700
So this can't be good.

817
00:37:13,500 --> 00:37:14,900
(Team P3)

818
00:37:14,900 --> 00:37:17,500
(70,000 dollars, 50,000 dollars,
50,000 dollars, 30,000 dollars)

819
00:37:17,500 --> 00:37:20,270
(Team P2's fund: 200,0000 dollars)

820
00:37:20,270 --> 00:37:22,840
If we got 200,000 dollars,
we're one of the teams at the bottom.

821
00:37:23,110 --> 00:37:24,740
- The lowest amount was 180,000 dollars.
- Really?

822
00:37:24,810 --> 00:37:26,310
How come it's lower than we expected?

823
00:37:26,550 --> 00:37:27,780
It's fine.

824
00:37:30,820 --> 00:37:32,120
Hello.

825
00:37:32,380 --> 00:37:33,820
- You're here.
- Hello.

826
00:37:33,820 --> 00:37:34,820
(Team P3, in 3rd place)

827
00:37:34,820 --> 00:37:37,090
- Hello. It's been a while.
- Good work.

828
00:37:37,390 --> 00:37:38,860
- Look at this.
- Hello.

829
00:37:38,860 --> 00:37:41,030
People from all three seasons are here.

830
00:37:41,030 --> 00:37:43,060
- People from all three seasons are here.
- Me? Gosh, no.

831
00:37:43,060 --> 00:37:44,600
- You didn't expect to see me?
- So this is Bloody Game?

832
00:37:44,600 --> 00:37:46,530
- Sang Min.
- This is crazy.

833
00:37:46,530 --> 00:37:48,100
Are you sure you want to be here?
This show is really tough.

834
00:37:48,200 --> 00:37:50,270
It was so interesting to see that...

835
00:37:50,270 --> 00:37:52,710
people from the three seasons
arrived in order.

836
00:37:52,870 --> 00:37:55,070
Yes. The experienced ones
ought to come in first.

837
00:37:55,070 --> 00:37:56,110
Or it would be embarrassing.

838
00:37:59,410 --> 00:38:01,580
I saw everyone's information on the cards.

839
00:38:02,080 --> 00:38:05,850
To be honest,
I thought either Team P1 or our team...

840
00:38:05,850 --> 00:38:07,420
would have the highest amount.

841
00:38:07,750 --> 00:38:09,920
Come on. I think our team...

842
00:38:09,920 --> 00:38:11,460
- No.
- No, it's not.

843
00:38:11,460 --> 00:38:13,630
- We picked ours. They picked yours.
- Wait.

844
00:38:13,630 --> 00:38:14,730
- These two are already picked.
- It wasn't a lot?

845
00:38:14,730 --> 00:38:16,130
No team has 280,000 dollars yet.

846
00:38:16,130 --> 00:38:18,030
They said they didn't get the highest one.

847
00:38:18,030 --> 00:38:19,930
So the remaining teams were...

848
00:38:19,930 --> 00:38:22,570
Team P2, Team C, and Team R.

849
00:38:22,570 --> 00:38:24,470
I told them it could be Team R.

850
00:38:24,500 --> 00:38:26,240
We could share that much.

851
00:38:26,310 --> 00:38:28,140
I was willing to share information
for some money...

852
00:38:28,140 --> 00:38:29,680
like 5,000 dollars in return.

853
00:38:29,680 --> 00:38:31,110
- Right.
- If I were to guess the team...

854
00:38:31,110 --> 00:38:34,380
with the highest amount, 280,000 dollars,

855
00:38:35,410 --> 00:38:36,450
what would you do for me?

856
00:38:37,080 --> 00:38:40,590
"We'll tell you which team to pick."

857
00:38:40,590 --> 00:38:41,750
"Give us money in return."

858
00:38:41,850 --> 00:38:44,690
Sang Min ambushed us with a deal.

859
00:38:44,720 --> 00:38:46,060
It has begun.

860
00:38:46,060 --> 00:38:50,030
His tactic to rope us in has begun.

861
00:38:50,030 --> 00:38:51,760
I saw you do this kind of thing a lot.

862
00:38:51,760 --> 00:38:53,130
- But I doubt you know for sure.
- No.

863
00:38:53,130 --> 00:38:54,670
- No. I'm serious.
- No, we know.

864
00:38:54,670 --> 00:38:56,170
We might know which one it is.

865
00:38:56,170 --> 00:38:57,640
No, I think I can figure it out too.

866
00:38:57,700 --> 00:38:58,940
- We know for sure.
- Really? Which one?

867
00:38:58,940 --> 00:38:59,970
It's Team R.

868
00:38:59,970 --> 00:39:01,110
It's Team R.

869
00:39:03,080 --> 00:39:04,840
He went like this.

870
00:39:05,180 --> 00:39:06,580
"How did he know?"

871
00:39:06,580 --> 00:39:07,780
It's obvious.

872
00:39:08,450 --> 00:39:09,880
- It's Team R?
- It has to be them.

873
00:39:09,880 --> 00:39:11,880
- It can't be them.
- Yes, it is.

874
00:39:13,820 --> 00:39:16,290
I kept telling them
our only option was Team R.

875
00:39:16,290 --> 00:39:18,090
Sang Min was like...

876
00:39:18,090 --> 00:39:19,960
"Oh, well... I..."

877
00:39:20,030 --> 00:39:23,400
I could sense that my hunch was right.

878
00:39:23,400 --> 00:39:25,360
I knew Team R had the highest team fund.

879
00:39:27,030 --> 00:39:28,870
Team P3, you're the 3rd team to arrive.

880
00:39:28,870 --> 00:39:31,040
Please pick the team fund you want.

881
00:39:34,370 --> 00:39:36,580
You chose Team Rookie's fund.

882
00:39:36,580 --> 00:39:38,640
(Team P3 chooses Team R's fund.)

883
00:39:38,640 --> 00:39:41,750
Team Rookie's fund is 280,000 dollars.

884
00:39:44,580 --> 00:39:46,490
The deity is still on our side.

885
00:39:46,590 --> 00:39:49,990
Xitsuh threw away the lock
without turning the numbers.

886
00:39:49,990 --> 00:39:52,560
I wondered if he did that
to make this happen.

887
00:39:52,560 --> 00:39:54,060
We came in third.

888
00:39:54,060 --> 00:39:56,630
But we got the best benefit.

889
00:39:56,630 --> 00:39:59,400
It was a reward
for playing the game properly.

890
00:39:59,400 --> 00:40:02,870
"You guys have been following
the right path."

891
00:40:02,870 --> 00:40:04,340
"I shall help you."

892
00:40:04,570 --> 00:40:05,570
(Team R)

893
00:40:05,570 --> 00:40:06,940
(120,000 dollars, 70,000 dollars,
70,000 dollars, 50,000 dollars)

894
00:40:06,940 --> 00:40:08,670
(120,000 dollars, 70,000 dollars,
70,000 dollars, 50,000 dollars)

895
00:40:08,670 --> 00:40:12,440
(Team P3's fund: 280,000 dollars)

896
00:40:12,440 --> 00:40:14,880
- Hey.
- So that's the highest amount?

897
00:40:14,880 --> 00:40:16,120
- Not the lowest?
- Jin Ho.

898
00:40:16,520 --> 00:40:17,850
Give us at least 10,000 dollars.

899
00:40:18,120 --> 00:40:19,950
- What do you mean?
- We gave you information.

900
00:40:19,950 --> 00:40:20,950
What?

901
00:40:20,950 --> 00:40:22,650
I didn't get any information from you.
What are you talking about?

902
00:40:22,650 --> 00:40:24,460
- We...
- What?

903
00:40:25,020 --> 00:40:27,630
Hye Seon. Give us 10,000 dollars.

904
00:40:27,760 --> 00:40:29,230
Why does he keep asking for money?

905
00:40:29,230 --> 00:40:30,260
- That's odd.
- I mean...

906
00:40:30,260 --> 00:40:31,260
We gave you information.

907
00:40:31,260 --> 00:40:32,770
I knew it. They're awful.

908
00:40:33,000 --> 00:40:34,300
You can't even spare that much?

909
00:40:35,230 --> 00:40:37,970
You guys got 280,000 dollars.
You can't give us 10,000 for our help?

910
00:40:38,340 --> 00:40:39,570
They didn't give us money.

911
00:40:39,570 --> 00:40:40,810
I even asked for just 5,000 dollars.

912
00:40:41,210 --> 00:40:42,880
They have to take the last one, right?

913
00:40:42,880 --> 00:40:44,640
- Right.
- Right?

914
00:40:44,710 --> 00:40:45,810
Hello.

915
00:40:45,810 --> 00:40:47,550
- Hello.
- Hello.

916
00:40:47,550 --> 00:40:49,010
- Hello.
- Good job.

917
00:40:49,010 --> 00:40:50,320
- Good work.
- Hello.

918
00:40:50,320 --> 00:40:52,020
- Hello.
- Gosh.

919
00:40:52,020 --> 00:40:53,250
- It's been a while.
- Nice to meet you.

920
00:40:53,250 --> 00:40:55,650
I thought that
Team C would perform better.

921
00:40:55,650 --> 00:40:57,490
Seeing Team C arrive in fourth place...

922
00:40:57,490 --> 00:40:59,390
was somewhat expected.

923
00:40:59,490 --> 00:41:01,660
I was hoping it would be Team Rookie.

924
00:41:01,790 --> 00:41:04,560
I was a bit disappointed.

925
00:41:04,560 --> 00:41:05,660
- What?
- Nice to meet you.

926
00:41:06,530 --> 00:41:07,700
- Hello.
- Nice to meet you.

927
00:41:10,900 --> 00:41:13,910
I thought
Team C would be a tough one to beat.

928
00:41:13,910 --> 00:41:15,440
They can't be written off that easily.

929
00:41:15,640 --> 00:41:18,240
They might be here to conquer this series.

930
00:41:19,010 --> 00:41:21,180
- Hello. I'm Kim You Hyun.
- Hello.

931
00:41:22,080 --> 00:41:23,250
Kim You Hyun is here.

932
00:41:25,220 --> 00:41:28,020
It would've been easier for us
if his team got eliminated first.

933
00:41:28,990 --> 00:41:30,120
A strong player is joining us.

934
00:41:31,020 --> 00:41:32,160
You've been well, right?

935
00:41:32,160 --> 00:41:33,290
Are you trying again...

936
00:41:47,370 --> 00:41:48,570
Well, Kyoung Hoon...

937
00:41:50,140 --> 00:41:52,210
He and I aren't...

938
00:41:52,780 --> 00:41:54,450
exactly on speaking terms.

939
00:41:55,510 --> 00:41:57,250
In the past, we've met on "The Genius."

940
00:41:58,150 --> 00:42:01,290
I really adored him.

941
00:42:02,590 --> 00:42:04,320
I saved him from getting eliminated.

942
00:42:05,220 --> 00:42:06,960
I did a lot for him.

943
00:42:07,460 --> 00:42:09,560
But in the end, he betrayed me...

944
00:42:10,160 --> 00:42:11,400
to save himself.

945
00:42:12,430 --> 00:42:14,270
I eliminated Sang Min...

946
00:42:14,270 --> 00:42:16,800
on a different survival game show
like this.

947
00:42:16,800 --> 00:42:19,270
He and I had been through thick and thin
on the show.

948
00:42:19,270 --> 00:42:21,940
He was eliminated
at the peak of his career.

949
00:42:21,940 --> 00:42:24,640
So that experience
must have traumatized him.

950
00:42:25,410 --> 00:42:27,480
That's what I mean to Sang Min.

951
00:42:35,220 --> 00:42:37,160
Team C, you're the fourth team to arrive.

952
00:42:37,160 --> 00:42:39,560
Please pick the team fund you want.

953
00:42:41,860 --> 00:42:43,630
He hasn't been going to games last year.

954
00:42:43,630 --> 00:42:44,860
I'll go with this.

955
00:42:46,370 --> 00:42:48,670
You chose your team for the fund.

956
00:42:48,670 --> 00:42:51,140
The fund of Team Challenger...

957
00:42:51,140 --> 00:42:53,210
is 240,000 dollars.

958
00:42:57,010 --> 00:42:59,240
I'm very happy with the fund.

959
00:42:59,240 --> 00:43:02,180
Looking at the amount,
we had to be in third place at least.

960
00:43:02,180 --> 00:43:04,520
I thought there was a high chance
we could be in second place.

961
00:43:04,520 --> 00:43:05,850
So I'm very happy with it.

962
00:43:06,220 --> 00:43:08,120
(Team C: Kim You Hyun, Kim Nam Hee,
Kim Kyoung Hoon, Kim Ji Hoo)

963
00:43:08,120 --> 00:43:10,020
(70,000 dollars, 70,000 dollars,
50,000 dollars, 50,000 dollars)

964
00:43:10,020 --> 00:43:13,530
(Team C's fund: 240,000 dollars)

965
00:43:13,960 --> 00:43:16,730
Fund selection for all the teams
is now complete.

966
00:43:17,160 --> 00:43:19,200
Please gather in the main hall.

967
00:43:20,030 --> 00:43:22,170
We're a real team now.

968
00:43:22,270 --> 00:43:23,900
We're sitting together as a team.

969
00:43:23,900 --> 00:43:26,240
- Look. They're scattered out.
- Exactly.

970
00:43:26,240 --> 00:43:27,910
- Look at us. We're like family.
- Yes.

971
00:43:27,910 --> 00:43:29,240
I really wanted to see you again.

972
00:43:29,240 --> 00:43:30,980
I'm so happy to see you again here.

973
00:43:30,980 --> 00:43:32,980
- We're on the same team.
- What is this? A school reunion?

974
00:43:32,980 --> 00:43:34,780
Being on the same team...

975
00:43:34,780 --> 00:43:36,380
got rid of all my frustration.

976
00:43:41,750 --> 00:43:43,820
The results of the game will be announced.

977
00:43:43,920 --> 00:43:47,130
The first team to arrive after the game...

978
00:43:47,790 --> 00:43:49,430
is Team P1.

979
00:43:49,430 --> 00:43:50,560
(Team P1, the winning team)

980
00:43:51,730 --> 00:43:53,670
And the losing team...

981
00:43:54,530 --> 00:43:55,930
is Team Rookie.

982
00:43:56,470 --> 00:43:57,640
Oh, no.

983
00:43:57,640 --> 00:44:00,110
Everyone on Team Rookie
is up for elimination.

984
00:44:00,110 --> 00:44:02,840
They cannot participate
in today's Money Challenge.

985
00:44:03,810 --> 00:44:06,380
It wasn't a big surprise
that Team R couldn't make it.

986
00:44:06,750 --> 00:44:08,310
I'm slightly happy that...

987
00:44:08,880 --> 00:44:10,380
we have an easy mark.

988
00:44:10,380 --> 00:44:13,390
You can't overlook the difference
between experienced ones and rookies.

989
00:44:14,090 --> 00:44:17,060
I feel bad for saying this, but
everyone on that team looks easy to beat.

990
00:44:17,160 --> 00:44:20,260
They never had to deal
with these ropes before.

991
00:44:20,260 --> 00:44:22,330
They didn't know what to do.

992
00:44:22,330 --> 00:44:23,830
They were a mess.

993
00:44:23,830 --> 00:44:25,660
I bet they were completely thrown off.

994
00:44:25,660 --> 00:44:28,700
I doubt they never had experience
solving problems like this.

995
00:44:28,800 --> 00:44:30,470
People often use this expression.

996
00:44:30,970 --> 00:44:32,140
"It hits the spot."

997
00:44:32,440 --> 00:44:33,670
"You should suffer too."

998
00:44:33,670 --> 00:44:34,970
Oh, how entertaining it is to watch them.

999
00:44:34,970 --> 00:44:36,140
But I don't want them to suffer
to this extent.

1000
00:44:36,140 --> 00:44:38,540
I don't want them to get sick
like catching a cold or getting injured.

1001
00:44:38,540 --> 00:44:39,750
I don't want that for them.

1002
00:44:39,750 --> 00:44:41,780
But I want them to suffer
right up until that moment.

1003
00:44:42,180 --> 00:44:43,820
I want them starving, exhausted...

1004
00:44:43,820 --> 00:44:45,280
and getting homesick...

1005
00:44:45,280 --> 00:44:47,350
and stressed that they can't sleep.

1006
00:44:47,350 --> 00:44:48,590
That's the sweet spot.

1007
00:44:48,590 --> 00:44:50,260
I don't want them to get sick or hurt.

1008
00:44:53,290 --> 00:44:56,630
(2 hours earlier)

1009
00:44:59,700 --> 00:45:00,770
My gosh.

1010
00:45:16,350 --> 00:45:18,080
- Darn.
- My feet can't move at all.

1011
00:45:20,650 --> 00:45:23,290
The high-speed team game is over.

1012
00:45:23,290 --> 00:45:24,420
I'm sorry.

1013
00:45:26,930 --> 00:45:28,260
It's all right.

1014
00:45:29,190 --> 00:45:32,560
You are the losing team
of the high-speed team game.

1015
00:45:33,100 --> 00:45:34,930
You will not be able to join...

1016
00:45:34,930 --> 00:45:37,070
the Money Challenge
which will be held in the Bloody Mansion.

1017
00:45:37,170 --> 00:45:40,870
You will have to survive
in the outdoor survival grounds.

1018
00:45:43,040 --> 00:45:44,980
Until the Deathmatch,

1019
00:45:44,980 --> 00:45:47,010
you can freely move around.

1020
00:45:52,720 --> 00:45:54,250
Darn it.

1021
00:45:59,060 --> 00:46:00,460
Let's take our time with it.

1022
00:46:03,200 --> 00:46:05,160
It hurt my pride.

1023
00:46:05,160 --> 00:46:07,500
It was demoralizing.

1024
00:46:07,500 --> 00:46:09,570
There were no rules.

1025
00:46:09,570 --> 00:46:12,940
I wanted to show people
that I could solve the problem fast.

1026
00:46:12,940 --> 00:46:15,170
But I couldn't do that.
So it was upsetting.

1027
00:46:15,170 --> 00:46:18,010
I was flustered too.

1028
00:46:18,810 --> 00:46:20,710
It was so embarrassing.

1029
00:46:20,750 --> 00:46:22,180
It was humiliating.

1030
00:46:22,180 --> 00:46:23,950
I couldn't keep my head up.

1031
00:46:23,980 --> 00:46:26,050
It was just pure humiliation.

1032
00:46:26,280 --> 00:46:28,950
If I tried to break out by force...

1033
00:46:28,950 --> 00:46:30,860
and helped my teammates,

1034
00:46:31,120 --> 00:46:32,990
we wouldn't have been in last place.

1035
00:46:34,130 --> 00:46:35,760
Let's just solve the problem.

1036
00:46:36,260 --> 00:46:40,370
But I kept trying to solve the problem.

1037
00:46:40,370 --> 00:46:42,270
For that, I felt like a complete idiot.

1038
00:46:42,730 --> 00:46:43,800
When everyone was leaving?

1039
00:46:43,800 --> 00:46:45,500
They didn't even look back.

1040
00:46:45,500 --> 00:46:46,670
Go!

1041
00:46:46,670 --> 00:46:49,010
(Team C escaped by a hair.)

1042
00:46:49,110 --> 00:46:50,380
We're the last ones.

1043
00:46:52,780 --> 00:46:54,510
But I remembered everyone's faces.

1044
00:46:54,810 --> 00:46:56,350
I don't need to play politics.

1045
00:46:56,350 --> 00:46:58,480
I should just kill them all
in the Deathmatch.

1046
00:46:58,780 --> 00:46:59,950
(Groaning)

1047
00:46:59,950 --> 00:47:01,750
You shouldn't have helped her.

1048
00:47:01,750 --> 00:47:03,490
You should've helped us.

1049
00:47:04,990 --> 00:47:06,260
(Sighing)

1050
00:47:06,260 --> 00:47:07,890
I was just infuriated.

1051
00:47:09,160 --> 00:47:10,330
Could you tell us what it is?

1052
00:47:10,760 --> 00:47:13,030
- Let me untie this first.
- Help me out. Then I'll tell you.

1053
00:47:13,060 --> 00:47:15,370
Hye Seon told me she'd give me a hint
if I helped them...

1054
00:47:15,370 --> 00:47:16,900
get out of the ropes.

1055
00:47:16,900 --> 00:47:18,470
So I was trying to help them get out.

1056
00:47:18,940 --> 00:47:20,370
I must have lost my mind.

1057
00:47:20,670 --> 00:47:22,170
I helped two of them get out.

1058
00:47:22,170 --> 00:47:23,810
Thinking back now, I must've lost my mind.

1059
00:47:24,440 --> 00:47:27,580
I didn't know
they'd stab me in the back like this.

1060
00:47:27,780 --> 00:47:30,350
I'm determined to get even...

1061
00:47:30,350 --> 00:47:32,320
with Hye Seon and Jin Ho.

1062
00:47:37,820 --> 00:47:39,860
- I should've used force.
- Thank you for your help.

1063
00:47:41,460 --> 00:47:43,560
- Nice to meet you.
- Good work.

1064
00:47:43,700 --> 00:47:44,830
- Nice to meet you.
- Good work.

1065
00:47:51,770 --> 00:47:53,170
This is infuriating.

1066
00:47:58,380 --> 00:47:59,640
It's freezing.

1067
00:48:01,350 --> 00:48:02,880
Darn it.

1068
00:48:05,720 --> 00:48:07,620
Gosh, this is crazy.

1069
00:48:08,450 --> 00:48:10,560
Hey, how are we going to stay here?

1070
00:48:31,210 --> 00:48:35,610
(The living area
for the outdoor survival grounds)

1071
00:48:50,500 --> 00:48:51,630
It's cold.

1072
00:48:54,770 --> 00:48:55,830
It's super cold.

1073
00:48:59,840 --> 00:49:01,010
Is this garlic?

1074
00:49:01,470 --> 00:49:02,710
We have to peel them?

1075
00:49:04,710 --> 00:49:06,510
Have garlic if you want to turn human.

1076
00:49:06,510 --> 00:49:08,050
I guess we have to peel them.

1077
00:49:09,110 --> 00:49:10,580
We have to use our fingers?

1078
00:49:11,750 --> 00:49:13,390
I've never done this before.

1079
00:49:13,390 --> 00:49:14,590
This is water.

1080
00:49:14,620 --> 00:49:16,720
(A box of bare essentials
is next to the garlic box.)

1081
00:49:17,790 --> 00:49:18,890
Potatoes.

1082
00:49:18,990 --> 00:49:21,330
They look like potatoes. What are they?

1083
00:49:21,330 --> 00:49:23,230
Darn it. They're raw potatoes.

1084
00:49:23,330 --> 00:49:24,800
- They're raw?
- Right.

1085
00:49:24,800 --> 00:49:26,330
- We need to start a fire.
- They're really raw.

1086
00:49:26,330 --> 00:49:27,600
We must start a fire.

1087
00:49:29,830 --> 00:49:31,700
I want to curse for real. Seriously.

1088
00:49:31,900 --> 00:49:33,100
- My gosh.
- Gosh.

1089
00:49:34,970 --> 00:49:36,440
The rules for the survival grounds.

1090
00:49:37,240 --> 00:49:39,880
(Basic Rules for Outdoor Survival Grounds)

1091
00:49:41,650 --> 00:49:42,950
(Reading)

1092
00:49:42,950 --> 00:49:44,950
- The names of the teams?
- Yes.

1093
00:49:45,520 --> 00:49:46,690
(Team R also gets the players' book.)

1094
00:49:46,690 --> 00:49:48,920
- I see. They were on the far left.
- Yes.

1095
00:49:48,920 --> 00:49:50,860
Kim Nam Hee.

1096
00:49:51,490 --> 00:49:52,820
- She's in Team Challenger?
- Yes.

1097
00:49:53,430 --> 00:49:54,830
Kang Ji Hoo.

1098
00:49:54,930 --> 00:49:57,560
Right. Our approach wasn't so smart.

1099
00:49:57,560 --> 00:50:00,470
We should've used any means
to get out of the ropes.

1100
00:50:00,470 --> 00:50:02,200
The first one...

1101
00:50:03,570 --> 00:50:04,900
What?

1102
00:50:04,900 --> 00:50:06,870
You graduated
from Seoul National University?

1103
00:50:07,640 --> 00:50:08,810
What?

1104
00:50:08,810 --> 00:50:09,840
I'm sorry.

1105
00:50:09,840 --> 00:50:11,380
You graduated
from Seoul National University?

1106
00:50:11,380 --> 00:50:12,910
I had no idea.

1107
00:50:12,910 --> 00:50:14,680
We have a strong team here.

1108
00:50:14,880 --> 00:50:16,680
We have someone from Mensa too.

1109
00:50:17,650 --> 00:50:19,320
Where should we put this?

1110
00:50:19,320 --> 00:50:21,220
Let's hang this up
since they're our targets.

1111
00:50:23,720 --> 00:50:25,620
All good. It's up now.

1112
00:50:26,190 --> 00:50:27,490
Let's kill them all.

1113
00:50:28,730 --> 00:50:30,960
- Nothing else?
- No, nothing else.

1114
00:50:33,030 --> 00:50:34,100
(The losing team will be kicked out
to the outdoor survival grounds.)

1115
00:50:34,100 --> 00:50:36,370
"On the first day, the losing team
of the high-speed team game..."

1116
00:50:36,370 --> 00:50:40,040
"will be released
to the outdoor survival grounds."

1117
00:50:41,170 --> 00:50:43,310
I guess it's just us here for today.

1118
00:50:43,310 --> 00:50:44,710
What?

1119
00:50:44,780 --> 00:50:45,940
It's...

1120
00:50:45,940 --> 00:50:47,650
It's just us here for today.

1121
00:50:47,650 --> 00:50:50,520
And we can only use coins here.

1122
00:50:50,780 --> 00:50:53,420
We can't use the coins we collect here
in the mansion.

1123
00:50:53,750 --> 00:50:55,550
- I think we should start...
- The coins...

1124
00:50:55,550 --> 00:50:57,320
- peeling the garlic.
- Wait. The garlic...

1125
00:50:57,420 --> 00:50:59,560
I think we should peel them
and collect coins.

1126
00:50:59,560 --> 00:51:01,030
So we can try to go big...

1127
00:51:01,030 --> 00:51:02,460
- at the Ghost Casino...
- Okay.

1128
00:51:02,560 --> 00:51:03,760
in the evening.

1129
00:51:04,030 --> 00:51:05,460
(The Ghost Casino is mentioned
in the rulebook.)

1130
00:51:05,460 --> 00:51:06,930
(The Ghost Casino will open once a day
in the outdoor survival grounds.)

1131
00:51:06,970 --> 00:51:09,130
We can use them later at the casino,
right?

1132
00:51:09,130 --> 00:51:10,500
- There has to be a reason.
- I think so.

1133
00:51:11,370 --> 00:51:13,040
Without the knife?

1134
00:51:14,940 --> 00:51:16,140
As for the skin...

1135
00:51:16,640 --> 00:51:18,440
They'll make perfect kindling.

1136
00:51:18,440 --> 00:51:20,010
- Let's gather them.
- Okay.

1137
00:51:20,680 --> 00:51:23,310
I didn't see this coming at all.

1138
00:51:23,310 --> 00:51:24,980
Same here. I didn't know we'd end up last.

1139
00:51:28,050 --> 00:51:30,590
My gosh, we're in the Garlic Inferno.

1140
00:51:31,960 --> 00:51:33,560
Oh, right.
They don't even give us our clothes.

1141
00:51:34,960 --> 00:51:36,730
They're going to sleep warm tonight,
right?

1142
00:51:38,530 --> 00:51:42,400
I expected to see Xitsuh and Jin Ho here.

1143
00:51:43,170 --> 00:51:44,670
- You expected to see some people.
- Yes.

1144
00:51:44,670 --> 00:51:46,070
- But...
- Jin Ho.

1145
00:51:46,070 --> 00:51:48,540
Well, everyone favors their friends.

1146
00:51:48,540 --> 00:51:50,240
Why don't we form an alliance for now?

1147
00:51:50,240 --> 00:51:52,780
- Yes. Let's play together if we can.
- Yes. Let's form an alliance.

1148
00:51:52,780 --> 00:51:53,780
Teams P2 and P3.

1149
00:51:53,780 --> 00:51:55,310
- The pure-bloods need to work together.
- Yes.

1150
00:51:55,310 --> 00:51:56,820
The pure-bloods need to work together.

1151
00:51:57,150 --> 00:52:00,550
And everyone from Team P1 is very good
at playing politics.

1152
00:52:01,050 --> 00:52:02,520
We need to stick together.

1153
00:52:02,520 --> 00:52:03,590
We must stay true to the games.

1154
00:52:03,590 --> 00:52:05,520
It can't be too political.

1155
00:52:05,620 --> 00:52:06,830
I can trust you.

1156
00:52:07,290 --> 00:52:10,330
- You know how it is.
- We see often outside the show.

1157
00:52:10,330 --> 00:52:11,560
I'm just single-minded.

1158
00:52:11,560 --> 00:52:13,830
Team P1...

1159
00:52:14,100 --> 00:52:16,530
has players who excel in playing politics.

1160
00:52:16,530 --> 00:52:18,570
The team has masters of politics.

1161
00:52:18,670 --> 00:52:21,710
I kept an eye on them
while keeping my guard up.

1162
00:52:21,710 --> 00:52:23,340
"We're all friends here."

1163
00:52:23,340 --> 00:52:26,480
"Let's help each other out when we can."

1164
00:52:26,510 --> 00:52:29,480
(Team P2's room, Team R's room,)

1165
00:52:29,480 --> 00:52:32,650
(Team P1's room, Team C's room,
Team P3's room)

1166
00:52:32,650 --> 00:52:34,020
Wait. That's the one?

1167
00:52:34,020 --> 00:52:35,190
Sang Min.

1168
00:52:38,320 --> 00:52:40,330
Okay. This is nice.

1169
00:52:40,860 --> 00:52:42,330
- There's more here.
- We're in.

1170
00:52:43,630 --> 00:52:46,330
How do you want to go about today's game?

1171
00:52:46,630 --> 00:52:48,730
- What kind of game will it be?
- I'm not sure about that.

1172
00:52:48,730 --> 00:52:50,070
We don't know what it is yet.

1173
00:52:50,070 --> 00:52:52,340
- I... Yes.
- Let me say this now.

1174
00:52:52,370 --> 00:52:55,570
You might see me cozying up
with certain teams.

1175
00:52:56,710 --> 00:52:58,210
- You can pretend to get the wrong idea.
- Okay.

1176
00:52:58,210 --> 00:53:00,040
- But never get the wrong idea.
- Okay.

1177
00:53:00,080 --> 00:53:03,110
Actually, I was really happy
to see you guys on my team.

1178
00:53:04,150 --> 00:53:07,090
I knew for sure that
you guys wouldn't betray the team.

1179
00:53:07,090 --> 00:53:09,120
Actually, Ji Min...

1180
00:53:09,520 --> 00:53:10,560
We should be careful.

1181
00:53:10,560 --> 00:53:11,590
No.

1182
00:53:13,930 --> 00:53:15,330
Gwan Hee might be able to win her over.

1183
00:53:17,360 --> 00:53:18,760
- Right.
- He's no joke.

1184
00:53:18,760 --> 00:53:19,760
He's good at winning girls over.

1185
00:53:19,760 --> 00:53:21,830
- We're lucky that he's not here today.
- Yes.

1186
00:53:23,870 --> 00:53:25,640
I'm glad she did this, though.

1187
00:53:25,640 --> 00:53:28,470
Ji Min gave Seung Jin the answer.

1188
00:53:28,470 --> 00:53:29,970
- They came in second thanks to her.
- Yes.

1189
00:53:30,480 --> 00:53:33,010
- They will at least trust us...
- Right.

1190
00:53:33,010 --> 00:53:34,710
for what she did.

1191
00:53:35,550 --> 00:53:37,580
Sang Min. Let's say...

1192
00:53:37,580 --> 00:53:40,290
you can only make an alliance
with one of the teams.

1193
00:53:40,550 --> 00:53:41,690
- Which...
- It must be Jin Ho's team for now.

1194
00:53:41,690 --> 00:53:42,720
- His team?
- Yes.

1195
00:53:43,090 --> 00:53:44,560
He and I have a good relationship too.

1196
00:53:45,660 --> 00:53:47,460
You Hyun's team might get carried away...

1197
00:53:47,460 --> 00:53:50,430
since it's their first time
on this series.

1198
00:53:52,360 --> 00:53:54,830
- Don't even get close to Kyoung Hoon.
- Right.

1199
00:53:55,370 --> 00:53:56,770
- who?
- Kyoung Hoon.

1200
00:53:56,900 --> 00:53:59,100
I'm sure he's here...

1201
00:53:59,440 --> 00:54:02,310
to get me eliminated.
That's what he came here for.

1202
00:54:03,910 --> 00:54:05,580
Was your name Ji Hoon?

1203
00:54:05,580 --> 00:54:07,380
- It's Ji Hoo. Kang Ji Hoo.
- Kang Ji Hoo.

1204
00:54:07,380 --> 00:54:09,280
- What year were you born?
- I was born in 2004.

1205
00:54:09,650 --> 00:54:11,080
You couldn't watch
the famous 2002 soccer game.

1206
00:54:11,280 --> 00:54:12,720
- No.
- That's crazy.

1207
00:54:12,720 --> 00:54:14,590
I've known You Hyun before.

1208
00:54:14,590 --> 00:54:17,190
I knew that his strong suit
was playing the numbers game.

1209
00:54:17,520 --> 00:54:19,020
So I was happy to see him on my team.

1210
00:54:19,020 --> 00:54:22,230
I liked that Ji Hoo was
the type of the youngest...

1211
00:54:22,230 --> 00:54:23,600
I love having on my team.

1212
00:54:23,760 --> 00:54:25,700
- You should take the bed.
- Gosh. No way.

1213
00:54:25,830 --> 00:54:27,630
I wouldn't feel comfortable.
I'll take this bed.

1214
00:54:27,900 --> 00:54:29,730
You're the youngest and the smart one.

1215
00:54:29,930 --> 00:54:33,940
You need to rest up well. That way,
you'll be ready to use your brain.

1216
00:54:33,940 --> 00:54:36,840
Ji Hoo went to KAIST.

1217
00:54:36,840 --> 00:54:38,740
He was born in 2004 or 2005.

1218
00:54:38,740 --> 00:54:40,650
I had a feeling
he would be a great asset to our team.

1219
00:54:40,650 --> 00:54:43,150
"Rest well,
and use your brain for the games."

1220
00:54:43,310 --> 00:54:45,350
We gave him the biggest bed.

1221
00:54:46,350 --> 00:54:47,890
- This doesn't feel right.
- What?

1222
00:54:47,990 --> 00:54:49,150
- Can't we play for it?
- No.

1223
00:54:49,420 --> 00:54:51,120
I'll massage your feet if you need.

1224
00:54:52,420 --> 00:54:53,730
It wasn't easy to turn it down.

1225
00:54:53,890 --> 00:54:56,160
Actually, I'm happy with it. I liked it.

1226
00:54:57,900 --> 00:55:02,830
(Team P3's room)

1227
00:55:04,840 --> 00:55:07,370
I had a low-key chat with Team P2
when I was downstairs.

1228
00:55:07,470 --> 00:55:08,710
That we should team up if necessary.

1229
00:55:09,310 --> 00:55:10,710
I also talked to Team P1.

1230
00:55:10,710 --> 00:55:12,110
It sounded like everyone wanted...

1231
00:55:13,040 --> 00:55:15,180
to get rid of Team C today.

1232
00:55:15,180 --> 00:55:16,250
Team C? Really?

1233
00:55:17,750 --> 00:55:19,980
(10 minutes ago)

1234
00:55:20,180 --> 00:55:21,390
Hello.

1235
00:55:22,090 --> 00:55:25,090
I see. You guys are staying in that room.

1236
00:55:26,560 --> 00:55:27,630
Sit down.

1237
00:55:27,930 --> 00:55:29,790
Should we get rid of Team C today?

1238
00:55:29,930 --> 00:55:31,000
No.

1239
00:55:32,260 --> 00:55:35,700
Why don't we have a nice time
with just the participants of this series?

1240
00:55:37,070 --> 00:55:38,070
We do need that.

1241
00:55:38,770 --> 00:55:39,800
Team C? Really?

1242
00:55:39,800 --> 00:55:41,640
And the participants of the series
can have a nice time together.

1243
00:55:44,780 --> 00:55:46,410
But that's bound to happen.

1244
00:55:47,250 --> 00:55:49,480
The other teams can see that
we perform well during games.

1245
00:55:49,580 --> 00:55:51,050
- We also get along with other people.
- And...

1246
00:55:51,420 --> 00:55:52,820
The team the others...

1247
00:55:52,820 --> 00:55:54,990
want to work with the most will be us.

1248
00:55:54,990 --> 00:55:56,020
- Yes.
- That's true.

1249
00:55:56,020 --> 00:55:57,760
Looking at the skill sets,

1250
00:55:57,760 --> 00:56:00,260
we definitely have an upper hand...

1251
00:56:00,390 --> 00:56:03,730
because each of us can focus
on the games well.

1252
00:56:03,830 --> 00:56:06,560
As they say,
we always pull our own weight or more.

1253
00:56:06,560 --> 00:56:08,130
Here's the thing.

1254
00:56:08,130 --> 00:56:09,200
If we make one wrong move...

1255
00:56:09,200 --> 00:56:11,070
when things are developing
in this early stage,

1256
00:56:11,240 --> 00:56:12,240
it could backfire.

1257
00:56:12,240 --> 00:56:13,840
"Forget it. Let's get rid of Team P3.
They're so snobby."

1258
00:56:13,840 --> 00:56:16,510
If the three teams come after us,
it could ruin us.

1259
00:56:17,010 --> 00:56:18,410
- So if we want to take the lead...
- That's a possibility.

1260
00:56:18,410 --> 00:56:19,840
from the get-go,

1261
00:56:20,240 --> 00:56:22,450
we should hook Team C and Team P2.

1262
00:56:22,450 --> 00:56:24,420
If we want to go hard from the get-go,

1263
00:56:24,420 --> 00:56:26,120
we could take Team P1 out.

1264
00:56:26,620 --> 00:56:28,520
I don't want to target any team.

1265
00:56:28,520 --> 00:56:30,190
- There's no choice.
- At least in the beginning.

1266
00:56:30,190 --> 00:56:31,360
But we don't have a choice.

1267
00:56:34,460 --> 00:56:37,560
Unless we want to stick
to a strict strategy,

1268
00:56:38,330 --> 00:56:39,360
we should play it safe.

1269
00:56:39,360 --> 00:56:40,700
- No. Here's what I think.
- But...

1270
00:56:40,700 --> 00:56:42,400
If we do that, we'd get swayed...

1271
00:56:42,400 --> 00:56:43,970
by Team P1's politics.

1272
00:56:44,170 --> 00:56:45,240
Seong Beom is...

1273
00:56:46,040 --> 00:56:47,370
like a picky prince.

1274
00:56:47,740 --> 00:56:49,740
Yes. He's a smart, but picky prince.

1275
00:56:50,140 --> 00:56:52,610
Once he's set on something...

1276
00:56:52,780 --> 00:56:55,710
"Yes. I'm right. I'm the best."
He doesn't listen to others.

1277
00:56:55,980 --> 00:56:57,550
Here's the thing about Xitsuh and me.

1278
00:56:57,780 --> 00:57:00,650
We were always at odds with each other.

1279
00:57:00,790 --> 00:57:04,420
Our personality and playing styles
don't match at all.

1280
00:57:04,660 --> 00:57:07,290
I thought, "Darn it. This is hard."

1281
00:57:07,730 --> 00:57:09,630
I'm not advocating that
we should get rid of Team P1.

1282
00:57:10,060 --> 00:57:12,230
Here's what we can do.
We can go to Team C.

1283
00:57:12,530 --> 00:57:13,970
"You're a target."

1284
00:57:13,970 --> 00:57:16,100
I think sharing that information
puts us in danger.

1285
00:57:16,370 --> 00:57:17,700
- Instead of that,
- But we should.

1286
00:57:17,840 --> 00:57:20,640
we can keep it light and say things...
"Why don't we work together?"

1287
00:57:20,640 --> 00:57:21,770
Because the moment we say...

1288
00:57:21,770 --> 00:57:24,540
No. It's the opposite. Asking them
to work with us is more dangerous...

1289
00:57:24,540 --> 00:57:25,580
because it would be our offer.

1290
00:57:25,580 --> 00:57:27,010
We need them to come to us for help.

1291
00:57:27,010 --> 00:57:28,910
We have to hook them,
so they're willing to do what we say.

1292
00:57:28,910 --> 00:57:31,020
Let's say we go with your tactic.
So they're a target.

1293
00:57:31,020 --> 00:57:32,380
"Who's targeting us?" "Team P1."

1294
00:57:32,380 --> 00:57:33,820
Then they'd go to Team P1.
"Are you coming after us?"

1295
00:57:33,820 --> 00:57:34,920
They'd ask, "Who told you that?"
"Team P3 told us."

1296
00:57:34,920 --> 00:57:35,990
That's what they'll say.

1297
00:57:36,250 --> 00:57:38,420
- That's why...
- If they're smart, they won't answer it.

1298
00:57:39,520 --> 00:57:41,890
This is your third time on this series.

1299
00:57:41,890 --> 00:57:43,260
Do people here think?

1300
00:57:44,560 --> 00:57:46,560
To speak from experience, Xitsuh...

1301
00:57:47,570 --> 00:57:49,570
keeps on talking
unless you tell him to stop.

1302
00:57:49,570 --> 00:57:51,470
He keeps sharing his thoughts.

1303
00:57:52,300 --> 00:57:56,040
And he rarely thinks that he can be wrong.

1304
00:57:56,240 --> 00:57:58,510
Making him see things clearly
takes a bit of time.

1305
00:57:58,610 --> 00:58:00,080
Seong Beom...

1306
00:58:00,650 --> 00:58:02,480
He knows that he's smart.

1307
00:58:03,110 --> 00:58:06,550
They're individuals
with strong personalities...

1308
00:58:07,080 --> 00:58:09,750
and aren't afraid
to express their opinions.

1309
00:58:09,750 --> 00:58:10,760
So there are too many cooks here.

1310
00:58:11,360 --> 00:58:12,560
That's a problem.

1311
00:58:13,260 --> 00:58:16,090
So I should work
on bringing them together.

1312
00:58:17,500 --> 00:58:19,330
Please gather in the main hall.

1313
00:58:22,400 --> 00:58:25,070
You know what I think? I don't think
Sang Min knows what he's in for.

1314
00:58:29,640 --> 00:58:31,910
The winning benefit
of today's Money Challenge...

1315
00:58:31,910 --> 00:58:33,010
will be announced.

1316
00:58:35,950 --> 00:58:38,050
The winning team
of today's Money Challenge...

1317
00:58:38,920 --> 00:58:40,890
will earn 50,000 dollars.

1318
00:58:41,420 --> 00:58:43,720
And the entire team
will be exempt from elimination.

1319
00:58:44,690 --> 00:58:45,990
Excluding the winning team,

1320
00:58:46,390 --> 00:58:48,430
a player from each team...

1321
00:58:49,290 --> 00:58:51,060
will be up for elimination.

1322
00:58:53,800 --> 00:58:54,830
Excluding the winning team,

1323
00:58:54,830 --> 00:58:56,630
anyone from the rest of the teams
could be an elimination candidate.

1324
00:58:56,630 --> 00:58:59,000
So we have to win first place.

1325
00:58:59,400 --> 00:59:01,610
Not ranking last would be more doable.

1326
00:59:01,610 --> 00:59:02,710
That can be done faster.

1327
00:59:02,710 --> 00:59:05,480
But if we have to be the winning team,
that's a big goal.

1328
00:59:06,110 --> 00:59:09,210
Today's Money Challenge will be revealed.

1329
00:59:10,450 --> 00:59:11,980
Today's Money Challenge is...

1330
00:59:13,720 --> 00:59:14,890
(Running Mate)

1331
00:59:14,890 --> 00:59:17,090
Running Mate.

1332
00:59:17,090 --> 00:59:19,560
(Running Mate)

1333
00:59:19,860 --> 00:59:22,460
Running Mate will be a team match.

1334
00:59:22,990 --> 00:59:24,960
This game requires
the players to score points...

1335
00:59:24,960 --> 00:59:26,930
through mind games
and strategic alliances.

1336
00:59:27,600 --> 00:59:31,870
Each team will be given 4 sets of cards
from 1 to 16 in different colors.

1337
00:59:32,870 --> 00:59:36,340
They will also be given two special cards.
A dictator card and an assassin card.

1338
00:59:36,640 --> 00:59:39,310
They will have a total of 66 cards.

1339
00:59:40,780 --> 00:59:42,850
The game consists of eight rounds.

1340
00:59:43,350 --> 00:59:45,920
A player from each team
will participate...

1341
00:59:46,020 --> 00:59:48,690
with eight cards every round.

1342
00:59:49,920 --> 00:59:53,090
Before the card game,
the Master of the round...

1343
00:59:53,220 --> 00:59:55,530
will be decided through Master Betting.

1344
00:59:56,960 --> 01:00:00,100
The first player will pick a master color
they want...

1345
01:00:00,260 --> 01:00:03,730
and predict the number of wins
in the round for the bet.

1346
01:00:04,640 --> 01:00:07,510
The next player can either
raise the number of wins...

1347
01:00:07,610 --> 01:00:09,570
from the previous player...

1348
01:00:09,770 --> 01:00:11,480
or give up on the bet.

1349
01:00:12,080 --> 01:00:14,750
Betting on zero wins...

1350
01:00:14,980 --> 01:00:17,980
trumps predicting eight wins.

1351
01:00:17,980 --> 01:00:19,580
(Green, 0 wins)

1352
01:00:19,580 --> 01:00:23,150
If every player gives up on the bet
except for one player...

1353
01:00:23,490 --> 01:00:26,360
or if a player bets on zero wins,
the very same player...

1354
01:00:26,360 --> 01:00:29,290
will become the Master
and the Master Betting will be complete.

1355
01:00:30,490 --> 01:00:33,760
Once the betting is complete,
the Master and the rest of the players...

1356
01:00:33,970 --> 01:00:36,030
will exchange a card each.

1357
01:00:37,200 --> 01:00:40,810
The Master will check the cards
from the three players...

1358
01:00:41,270 --> 01:00:45,010
and distribute one card to each player
from their own set of cards.

1359
01:00:45,940 --> 01:00:47,710
Once the exchange is over,

1360
01:00:47,850 --> 01:00:50,250
the Master can nominate a mate.

1361
01:00:51,120 --> 01:00:54,590
To do so, the Master will pick
a number from 1 to 16.

1362
01:00:54,790 --> 01:00:56,820
During the card game,
the first player who submits...

1363
01:00:56,850 --> 01:00:58,790
the chosen card by the Master...

1364
01:00:58,790 --> 01:01:01,690
will be the Master's mate.

1365
01:01:01,690 --> 01:01:02,830
(Mate)

1366
01:01:02,830 --> 01:01:05,360
However, the Master can skip
nominating their mate...

1367
01:01:05,360 --> 01:01:07,970
if they don't wish to do so.

1368
01:01:09,470 --> 01:01:12,200
Each round will consist of eight sets.

1369
01:01:12,800 --> 01:01:15,740
For the first set,
the Master will play their card first.

1370
01:01:15,940 --> 01:01:18,180
Afterward,
the winner of the previous set...

1371
01:01:18,180 --> 01:01:21,510
will get to play their card first
for the next set.

1372
01:01:22,480 --> 01:01:24,480
Once the first player submit their card,

1373
01:01:24,520 --> 01:01:26,980
the color of the played card
will be the lead color.

1374
01:01:27,650 --> 01:01:29,850
The rest of the players must submit...

1375
01:01:29,850 --> 01:01:32,590
the cards in the same color
as the lead color.

1376
01:01:32,960 --> 01:01:35,030
Only when a player doesn't have any card
in the same color,

1377
01:01:35,190 --> 01:01:37,460
they can submit a card
of a different color.

1378
01:01:38,330 --> 01:01:41,530
However, as for special cards such as
the dictator card and the assassin card,

1379
01:01:41,670 --> 01:01:44,740
they can be played anytime
regardless of the lead color.

1380
01:01:45,170 --> 01:01:48,210
If the first player presents
a special card,

1381
01:01:48,370 --> 01:01:51,880
there won't be any designated lead color
for the round.

1382
01:01:52,540 --> 01:01:54,550
Once everyone submits their card,

1383
01:01:54,550 --> 01:01:57,520
the winner will be decided
based on the value of the cards.

1384
01:01:58,450 --> 01:02:01,350
For example,
the player with a dictator card...

1385
01:02:01,650 --> 01:02:03,420
will win the set.

1386
01:02:04,290 --> 01:02:07,990
But if the dictator and assassin cards
are both played in the same round,

1387
01:02:08,360 --> 01:02:11,030
the player with the assassin card
will win the set.

1388
01:02:12,000 --> 01:02:14,700
In the absence of a dictator card,

1389
01:02:14,700 --> 01:02:17,740
the player with the highest card
in the master color wins.

1390
01:02:18,570 --> 01:02:21,540
If none of the cards are
in the master color,

1391
01:02:21,540 --> 01:02:24,640
the player with the highest card
in the lead color wins the set.

1392
01:02:25,540 --> 01:02:28,780
If there's a tie between two players,

1393
01:02:28,910 --> 01:02:31,480
the player who submits their card first
wins the set.

1394
01:02:32,280 --> 01:02:34,350
Before reaching the eighth set,

1395
01:02:34,350 --> 01:02:36,850
when it becomes impossible
for the Master...

1396
01:02:36,850 --> 01:02:38,320
to reach the predicted number of wins,

1397
01:02:38,460 --> 01:02:42,190
the rest of the sets will not continue.
The round will end immediately.

1398
01:02:43,130 --> 01:02:47,000
Once the round is over, the points
will be distributed accordingly.

1399
01:02:47,400 --> 01:02:51,840
The number of wins the Master predicts
will be base points for the round.

1400
01:02:52,140 --> 01:02:54,710
Each round,
additional points will be added...

1401
01:02:54,710 --> 01:02:56,440
to the base points.

1402
01:02:57,310 --> 01:02:59,310
If the Master successfully predicts
the number of wins,

1403
01:02:59,680 --> 01:03:02,650
the Master and their mate
will split the winning points evenly.

1404
01:03:02,980 --> 01:03:04,720
The remaining point will be discarded.

1405
01:03:05,350 --> 01:03:07,080
If the Master didn't have a mate,

1406
01:03:07,220 --> 01:03:09,890
they will take all the points.

1407
01:03:10,620 --> 01:03:12,560
If the Master's prediction fails,

1408
01:03:12,660 --> 01:03:15,260
everyone except for the Master
and their mate...

1409
01:03:15,260 --> 01:03:16,890
will split the points evenly.

1410
01:03:17,800 --> 01:03:20,900
If the Master bets on zero wins,

1411
01:03:21,270 --> 01:03:23,270
the base points will be ten.

1412
01:03:23,730 --> 01:03:25,840
If the Master's prediction fails,

1413
01:03:25,840 --> 01:03:28,240
the Master and their mate will lose...

1414
01:03:28,440 --> 01:03:31,140
the same number of points
the other two players gain.

1415
01:03:31,810 --> 01:03:35,280
Following these rules,
once all eight rounds are over,

1416
01:03:35,280 --> 01:03:38,450
the winning team will be decided
after a comparison of all team points.

1417
01:03:38,450 --> 01:03:39,880
(The winning team will be decided
after a comparison of all team points.)

1418
01:03:40,350 --> 01:03:43,820
There are three types of items
for Running Mate.

1419
01:03:44,920 --> 01:03:47,990
The first item is the reverse card.

1420
01:03:48,360 --> 01:03:50,490
The card reveal order of the round...

1421
01:03:50,760 --> 01:03:52,830
is changed counterclockwise.

1422
01:03:53,530 --> 01:03:56,770
The second item is the extra card ticket.

1423
01:03:57,170 --> 01:03:59,240
An extra card can be added...

1424
01:03:59,240 --> 01:04:01,070
in the selected round.

1425
01:04:01,810 --> 01:04:03,970
The third item is a hidden item.

1426
01:04:04,140 --> 01:04:06,180
It will get revealed before Round Five.

1427
01:04:06,180 --> 01:04:07,750
(Hidden item, revealed before Round 5,
cost of 20,000 dollars)

1428
01:04:07,850 --> 01:04:09,810
After playing the first card,

1429
01:04:10,010 --> 01:04:12,120
winning rounds while the rules enhance...

1430
01:04:12,220 --> 01:04:14,990
is called a trick-taking game.

1431
01:04:14,990 --> 01:04:17,090
I realized that the game
was that type of game.

1432
01:04:17,290 --> 01:04:20,060
However, it will be hard to win
when there are four people.

1433
01:04:20,420 --> 01:04:22,490
Simply put, it's "Make good friends."

1434
01:04:22,490 --> 01:04:24,230
It's a game about working with a friend,

1435
01:04:24,360 --> 01:04:27,460
but you don't know
who will become your friend.

1436
01:04:27,570 --> 01:04:30,300
In the end,
predicting the winning rounds...

1437
01:04:30,300 --> 01:04:32,870
and taking the win is very difficult.

1438
01:04:33,240 --> 01:04:36,440
I thought it was another team game.

1439
01:04:36,810 --> 01:04:39,310
I realized it was a game of politics.

1440
01:04:39,480 --> 01:04:41,880
There are many games
with winning formulas in "The Genius."

1441
01:04:42,110 --> 01:04:44,650
That was why I naturally started
by thinking if this game...

1442
01:04:44,650 --> 01:04:46,450
had winning formulas,

1443
01:04:46,680 --> 01:04:48,420
but that wasn't the case.

1444
01:04:48,550 --> 01:04:52,120
The most important thing was to know
how to shake up the other team.

1445
01:04:52,290 --> 01:04:54,660
I thought that was
the winning formula of this game.

1446
01:04:56,260 --> 01:04:58,760
After a free meeting session,

1447
01:04:58,900 --> 01:05:01,100
players must submit
the order of participation.

1448
01:05:05,000 --> 01:05:06,840
- You were there, right?
- Yes.

1449
01:05:07,910 --> 01:05:09,040
Well,

1450
01:05:09,410 --> 01:05:11,240
teaming up doesn't have that much meaning,

1451
01:05:12,510 --> 01:05:13,940
but let's be warm with each other.

1452
01:05:13,940 --> 01:05:15,650
- That would be great.
- Nice and warm.

1453
01:05:16,850 --> 01:05:17,880
Right?

1454
01:05:18,520 --> 01:05:21,850
It's a game that's just played
how we know it is.

1455
01:05:22,720 --> 01:05:23,850
But what's important...

1456
01:05:24,860 --> 01:05:26,620
is how to play tricks...

1457
01:05:27,160 --> 01:05:29,790
how to plan out the strategy.

1458
01:05:29,790 --> 01:05:31,830
That's the only thing I'm thinking about.

1459
01:05:32,300 --> 01:05:34,730
Everyone wants to start out strong...

1460
01:05:34,730 --> 01:05:37,270
- right at the start of Round One.
- Right.

1461
01:05:37,370 --> 01:05:40,300
Most will want the good players...

1462
01:05:40,470 --> 01:05:42,070
to play 1 and 2,

1463
01:05:42,070 --> 01:05:43,770
or 1 and 8.

1464
01:05:43,770 --> 01:05:45,110
- Right.
- Right.

1465
01:05:45,340 --> 01:05:47,980
This game is meaningless
if you don't place first.

1466
01:05:48,380 --> 01:05:51,950
Even while facing the risk
of placing last,

1467
01:05:51,950 --> 01:05:54,220
the game must be planned to place first.

1468
01:05:54,220 --> 01:05:57,520
But there are extra points earned
in the latter rounds.

1469
01:05:57,520 --> 01:05:59,090
For the latter rounds,

1470
01:05:59,090 --> 01:06:01,730
people with good decision-making
must be positioned.

1471
01:06:01,990 --> 01:06:04,360
So Jeong Keun Woo will go out
for Round 2 and Round 3.

1472
01:06:04,860 --> 01:06:06,360
Park Ji Min will go out for
Round 4 and Round 5.

1473
01:06:06,630 --> 01:06:08,170
Lee Sang Min will go out for
Round 6 and Round 7.

1474
01:06:08,170 --> 01:06:10,830
And I will go out for the final round,
Round Eight.

1475
01:06:11,900 --> 01:06:13,900
- It's 1 of these 2 for them.
- Right.

1476
01:06:14,540 --> 01:06:15,570
Here as well.

1477
01:06:16,410 --> 01:06:18,910
It's either Hong Jin Ho or Heo Seong Beom.

1478
01:06:19,810 --> 01:06:21,450
Xitsuh could be an option as well.

1479
01:06:22,380 --> 01:06:24,010
I'm not sure about Kang Ji Hoo.

1480
01:06:26,450 --> 01:06:29,190
Ji Hoo might be smarter than You Hyun.

1481
01:06:29,950 --> 01:06:32,660
Kang Ji Hoo is a mysterious one.

1482
01:06:33,260 --> 01:06:34,830
He looks so serious...

1483
01:06:36,130 --> 01:06:37,800
and smart.

1484
01:06:37,900 --> 01:06:40,970
Ji Hoo is my junior. My junior from KAIST.

1485
01:06:40,970 --> 01:06:42,930
He's a bit of a geek.

1486
01:06:42,930 --> 01:06:44,640
He has that typical geekiness...

1487
01:06:44,640 --> 01:06:46,540
of an engineering student from KAIST.

1488
01:06:46,740 --> 01:06:49,240
He can bounce here and there
like a rugby ball.

1489
01:06:49,440 --> 01:06:51,510
He can be unpredictable.

1490
01:06:51,710 --> 01:06:53,580
(Team C's room)

1491
01:06:53,580 --> 01:06:55,050
"When picking a Mate,"

1492
01:06:55,910 --> 01:06:58,450
"the Master calls out a number
between 1 to 16."

1493
01:06:59,280 --> 01:07:01,720
"The Master calls out a number
between 1 to 16."

1494
01:07:02,450 --> 01:07:05,260
I have great observations.
There's a certain point about geniuses.

1495
01:07:05,320 --> 01:07:06,990
I'm not sure if this is scientific,

1496
01:07:07,190 --> 01:07:08,490
but their brains look bigger.

1497
01:07:09,030 --> 01:07:10,360
The back of his head looks slightly big.

1498
01:07:11,000 --> 01:07:12,500
He looks like one
with a good brain capacity.

1499
01:07:12,660 --> 01:07:13,700
(Using his big brain in full power)

1500
01:07:13,700 --> 01:07:14,930
The best could be around three.

1501
01:07:15,430 --> 01:07:17,300
Three? Three or four.

1502
01:07:17,570 --> 01:07:18,570
Three or four?

1503
01:07:19,000 --> 01:07:20,640
The rules were very complicated.

